http://www.cnn.com/entertainment|http://www.cnn.com/2018/09/07/entertainment/geoffrey-owens-tyler-perry-job-offer/index.html||entertainment,'Cosby' star accepts Tyler Perry's job offer - CNN|2018-09-07|Chloe Melas||(CNN) Actor Geoffrey Owens has gone from being job-shamed to landing a major Hollywood gig.

A representative for Owens told CNN that he has accepted a job offer from Tyler Perry, who tweeted earlier this week that he wanted Owens to appear on his OWN television show, "The Haves and The Have Nots."

Owen's exact role on the show is unknown, but he'll appear on multiple episodes.

#GeoffreyOwens I'm about to start shootings OWN's number one drama next week! Come join us!!! I have so much respect for people who hustle between gigs. The measure of a true artist. â€” Tyler Perry (@tylerperry) September 4, 2018

Owens, who rose to fame as Elvin Tibideaux on "The Cosby Show" from 1985 to 1992, made headlines recently after photos of the actor working at a Trader Joe's a grocery store were first published by the Daily Mail.

Owens told CNN in an interview on Tuesday that while he was initially devastated by the job-shaming attention, the support he received on social media was overwhelmingly positive.

